House Resolution 514
By: Representative Powell of the 33rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Bobby C. Pate; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Bobby C. Pate on September 28, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Bobby C. Pate was born on November 29, 1936, in Jacksonville, Florida, a
5 beloved son of Richard Pate and Ada Dukes Pate Jeffries; and
6 WHEREAS, he was a gifted athlete who played college football at South Georgia State
7 College under thenâ€“head coach Bobby Bowden before transferring to Presbyterian College,
8 where he was twice named Player of the Year and South Carolina Back of the Year; and
9 WHEREAS, his athletic talent earned him selection in both the 1960 NFL Draft by the San
10 Francisco 49ers and the 1960 American Football League Draft by the Boston Patriots; and
11 WHEREAS, following his playing career, he dedicated himself to coaching, beginning as an
12 assistant football coach and head track coach at Hart County High School from 1963 to 1965
13 before serving as head coach and athletic director at Toccoa High School, Norcross High
14 School, and Cherokee High School between 1965 and 1974; and
