15 WHEREAS, he transitioned into college coaching as an assistant coach at Western Carolina
16 University from 1974 to 1979 and later earned his first collegiate head coaching position at
17 the University of West Georgia, where he led the team to an NCAA Division III National
18 Championship in 1982; and
19 WHEREAS, he later returned to Hart County in the mid-1980s to serve as head coach of the
20 Hart County Bulldogs, leading and mentoring young athletes for several years before his
21 retirement; and
22 WHEREAS, he was united in love and marriage to his wife, Donna, with whom he shared
23 63 wonderful years, and the two were blessed with three remarkable children, Elliott, Kathee,
24 and Lonn; and
25 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Bobby C. Pate will long be remembered
26 for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who had the great
27 fortune of knowing him.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Bobby C. Pate and express
30 their deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
33 family of Bobby C. Pate.
